Process called "fetch_one_sqlite_row" that takes cursor as Any returns Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]]:
    Note: Fetch one row from executed query
    Try:
        Let all_rows be fetch_all_sqlite_rows with cursor as cursor
        If length of all_rows is greater than 0:
            Return all_rows at index 0
        Return none
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Return none

Process called "get_sqlite_affected_rows" that takes cursor as Any returns Integer:
    Note: Get number of affected rows from last operation
    Try:
        If cursor is none or not cursor["executed"]:
            Return 0
        
        Note: This would call sqlite3_changes()
        Let query be cursor["last_query"] as String
        If starts_with with text as query and prefix as "INSERT" or starts_with with text as query and prefix as "UPDATE" or starts_with with text as query and prefix as "DELETE":
            Return 1  Note: Simulate one affected row
        
        Return 0
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Return 0

Process called "get_sqlite_last_insert_id" that takes cursor as Any returns Optional[Integer]:
    Note: Get last inserted row ID
    Try:
