Process called "determine_sqlite_query_type" that takes query as String returns String:
    Note: Determine the type of SQL query
    Try:
        Let query_upper be to_uppercase with text as trim_whitespace with text as query
        
        If starts_with with text as query_upper and prefix as "SELECT":
            Return "SELECT"
        Otherwise if starts_with with text as query_upper and prefix as "INSERT":
            Return "INSERT"
        Otherwise if starts_with with text as query_upper and prefix as "UPDATE":
            Return "UPDATE"
        Otherwise if starts_with with text as query_upper and prefix as "DELETE":
            Return "DELETE"
        Otherwise if starts_with with text as query_upper and prefix as "CREATE":
            Return "CREATE"
        Otherwise if starts_with with text as query_upper and prefix as "DROP":
            Return "DROP"
        Otherwise if starts_with with text as query_upper and prefix as "ALTER":
            Return "ALTER"
        
        Return "OTHER"
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Return "UNKNOWN"

Process called "count_query_placeholders" that takes query as String returns Integer:
    Note: Count parameter placeholders (?) in query
    Try:
        Let count be 0
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than length of query:
            Let char be get_character_at_position with text as query and position as i
            If char is equal to "?":
                Set count to count plus 1
            Set i to i plus 1
        Return count
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Return 0

Process called "starts_with" that takes text as String and prefix as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if text starts with prefix
    If length of text is less than length of prefix:
        Return false
    
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than length of prefix:
        Let text_char be get_character_at_position with text as text and position as i
        Let prefix_char be get_character_at_position with text as prefix and position as i
        If text_char is not equal to prefix_char:
            Return false
        Set i to i plus 1
    
    Return true

